<p>I think itâ€™s okay to make something that nobody wants. All you need to do is to make sure youâ€™ve fully expressed your emotions in this product.</p>

<p>But in most cases, people care too much or think too much, and end up making something even they themselves donâ€™t like it.</p>

<p>If everyone made things they really liked, weâ€™d have a lot more cool stuff.</p>

<p>This is tougher than it seems. Because if you have expectations, you get worried, stressed, and lose your feelings right away.</p>

<p>In simpler terms, people canâ€™t make something they donâ€™t like and hope others will like it.</p>

<p>Maybe thatâ€™s why a lot of cool stuff started as side projects. People donâ€™t expect much from side projects; they do it more for fun or for themselves.</p>

